# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Calculating sum upto current index in curr and having total sum in s. at every index we are checking `abs(curr_sum/curr_idx+1, total_sum-curr/n-curr_idx-1)` with min we have i.e `mn` in following code. we are storing index with minimum avg in `idx`.
In code checking the condition `i!=n-1` take care of n - curr_idx - 1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
`O(N)` - we are traversing only once.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
`O(1)` We are not using any extra space.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumAverageDifference(vector<int>& nums) {
        long int s =0,curr =0;   // s-> total_sum, cuur-> sum upto curr index
        int mn = INT_MAX,idx =0,n = nums.size();

        for(int i:nums) s+=i;    //calculating total sum

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            curr+= nums[i];
            s-=nums[i];
            if(i!=n-1){
                if(mn>abs(curr/(i+1) - (s/(n-i-1)))){
                    mn = abs(curr/(i+1) - (s/(n-i-1)));
                    idx= i;
                }
            } 
            else{                       //i = n-1
                if(mn>curr/(i+1)){
                    mn = curr/n;
                    idx= i;
                    }
            }
        }
        return idx;
    }
};
```

